; Per PR-4 of #1262: the canonical form strips thousands-separator
; commas from numeric literals. `1,024` and `1024` parse to the same
; Amount; the formatter emits one of them.
;
; This fixture documents the choice. The dispute is tracked in
; #1252 and (if reopened) any successor - preserving the user's
; lexical form would require extending the typed AST to carry a
; had-comma flag, which is a #1262 phase-5+ refactor.
2024-01-01 open Assets:Money

2024-07-20 * "comma-bearing amount"
  Assets:Money  -1024 USD
  Expenses:Thingamabobs
